/*!
\page os_fullfile FULLFILE Build a Full Filename From Pieces

<p>
Section: \ref sec_os "Operating System Functions"
\section Usage
The <tt>fullfile</tt> routine constructs a full filename from a set of
pieces, namely, directory names and a filename.  The syntax is:
\verbatim
  x = fullfile(dir1,dir2,...,dirn,filename)
\endverbatim
where each of the arguments are strings.  The <tt>fullfile</tt> function
is equivalent to <tt>[dir1 dirsep dir2 dirsep ... dirn dirsep filename]</tt>.
\section Example

